VNC Debug
---------

You can use VNC-Viewer in Windows to control Chipsee Raspberry Pi product over Ethernet.

Continue the debugging by follow these steps:

* Enable the VNC feature in the Chipsee Raspberry |Pi| product by running the following command in debug console:
    .. code:: bash

        $ sudo raspi-config

        Interfacing Options -> VNC -> Yes

* If you donâ€™t have a debug console, you can also use the GUI feature to enable VNC.
    .. figure:: /Media/Pi/Software/VNC_Debug.jpeg
       :align: center
       :figclass: align-center

    .. figure:: /Media/Pi/Software/VNC_Debug_2.jpeg
       :align: center
       :figclass: align-center

       Enabling VNC (GUI)

* Use VNC-Viewer in Windows to control it over Ethernet, as shown in the figures below.
    .. figure:: /Media/Pi/Software/VNC_Debug_3.jpeg
       :align: center
       :figclass: align-center

       Vnc-Viewer Connect

    .. figure:: /Media/Pi/Software/VNC_Debug_4.jpeg
       :align: center
       :figclass: align-center

       Authentications

    .. figure:: /Media/Pi/Software/VNC_Debug_5.jpeg
       :align: center
       :figclass: align-center

       VNC Desktop

